| Fields of employment | Science, technology, engineering, industry, military, exploration |

[Computer engineering](/Computer_engineering) (CE, [a] CoE, CpE, or CompE) is a branch of [engineering](/Engineering) specifically tailored for those who find the inherent complexities of both [computer hardware](/Computer_hardware) and [software](/Software) equally fascinating and infuriating. It's where the abstract logic of computation collides, often violently, with the stubborn realities of physical electronics. This isn't just about making things work; it's about making them work *together*, a feat often requiring the patience of a saint and the diagnostic skills of a seasoned detective.

This article is part of [a series](/Category:Engineering) on [Engineering](/Engineering), a vast and sometimes bewildering collection of human endeavors to bend the natural world to our will.

